cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR 

This paper deals with user modeling and analysis of social media data, which falls under the sub-categories of social media analysis (cs.SI), natural language processing (cs.CL), social and information networks (cs.SOC), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper specifically focuses on analyzing discussions and opinions related to polarized political events, which is a common topic in social media analysis and information retrieval research.
